description:
This pair of pirate spiders (Mimetus sp.) were found under the eaves of a house. In addition to their diagnostic shape, the female was resting behind her distinctive egg sac. Members of the genus Mimetus place their eggs in a cocoon of thick, loosely wraped, coppery-orange silk.

While this is most likely the widespread species M. hesperus, there are thought to be several undescribed species of Mimetus in California and without examining the spiders reproductive structures under a microscope I can not be 100% certain of their ID.
